[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mA [0m[38;5;252;3mQuickonf[0m[38;5;252m configuration file is composed of multiple sections, called groups. The group name starts at the beginning of the line, instructions are indented.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mgroup name[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  instruction A[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  instruction B[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  ...[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  instruction G[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m    instruction H depending on instruction G[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m    instruction I depending on instruction G[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mIndentations length and type (spaces or tabs) is not strict, you may use whichever you want. Keep in mind that, when mixing indentations, tabs are considered to be equivalent to aligning to multiples of 8 spaces (ie. [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m <space><space><tab> [0m[38;5;252m is equivalent to 8 spaces).                                                                                                                                                             [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSome instructions have an impact on multiple other instructions, like conditional execution ([0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m if [0m[38;5;252m) or repetition ([0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m repeat [0m[38;5;252m), in this case you must use a 2nd indentation level (or even more). See below for examples.                                                                                                                                                                                                                 [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1m Commands [0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mThe most important type of instruction is the commands. There are many available commands, and probably many more to come. A command is the instruction given to [0m[38;5;252;3mQuickonf[0m[38;5;252m for system checking and modification. The commands may need arguments and may return output values (see [0m[38;5;252;3mVariables[0m[38;5;252m below). See the [0m[38;5;252;3mCommands[0m[38;5;252m section for details on how to use commands.                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mBy convention, commands modifying data only for one user are prefixed with "[0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m user. [0m[38;5;252m" and take the username as their first argument. Other commands modify system-wide values.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1m Variables [0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSome commands return output values, that can be stored in variables if needed. Variables are named with alphanumerical characters. Syntax to store values is the following:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mgroup name[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  var1 var2 = command arg1 arg2[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mUsing variables after assignment is as simple as putting the variable name between "<" and ">" anywhere, like:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mgroup name[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  var = command1 arg1 arg2[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  command2 <var>[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m... here, the first output of the first command is used as the argument of the second command.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mExcept for the following global ones, variables are limited to their groups: there is no risk of conflict between variables in different groups.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;39;1m## Global variables[0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSome global variables are set when [0m[38;5;252;3mQuickonf[0m[38;5;252m starts:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m hostname [0m[38;5;252m: the hostname of the computer                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m oscodename [0m[38;5;252m: the codename of the current operating system version                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m confdir [0m[38;5;252m: path of the directory containing the configuration file (can be used to read other files in the same directory, templates etc)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;39;1m## Expanding variables content[0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSometimes, a variable's content refers to other variables. Take for instance a file that contains variables names. If you read the file with the [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m file.read [0m[38;5;252m command, it may be stored in a variable, but the content of the read file is not processed for variables names. In order to process variables names references inside a variable content, simply use the [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m expand [0m[38;5;252m instruction with the variable name as its only argument.[0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mExample:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mAPT sources[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  aptsrc = file.read <confdir>/sources.list.tmpl[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  expand aptsrc[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  file.content /etc/apt/sources.list <aptsrc>[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m... here, the [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m sources.list.tmpl [0m[38;5;252m file may contain [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m <oscodename> [0m[38;5;252m.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1m Conditional execution [0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mInstructions can be grouped below a [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m if [0m[38;5;252m instruction, which executes then only if the condition is true.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSupported conditions are:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m file.absent </path/to/file> [0m[38;5;252m: true if the file does not exist                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m file.present </path/to/file> [0m[38;5;252m: true if the file exists                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m <value1> = <value2> [0m[38;5;252m: true if values are equal (compared as strings)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                [0m
[38;5;252m• [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m <value1> != <value2> [0m[38;5;252m: true if values are different (compared as strings)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mExample:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mVPN[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m  if <hostname> = mylaptop[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251m    nm.import openvpn <confdir>/myvpn.ovpn[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252m... here, the [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m nm.import openvpn <confdir>/myvpn.ovpn [0m[38;5;252m is only executed if the host name is "mylaptop". You may of course put multiple instructions with the 2nd indentation level.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    [0m
[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      [0m
[0m[38;5;228;48;5;63;1m Repeating identical commands and arguments [0m[38;5;252m[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          [0m
[0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mSay you want to apply similar commands multiple times. Instead of writing the same prefix in multiple lines, you can use the [0m[38;5;203;48;5;236m repeat [0m[38;5;252m instruction. It makes it easier to write and to read your configuration file. It takes as arguments the command to be repeated, optionally with its first arguments.                                                                                                                             [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252;3mQuickonf[0m[38;5;252m translates it by prepending this command name and these arguments to all lines.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;252mExample:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               [0m
[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       [0m
[38;5;251m[0m[38;5;252m  [0m[38;5;251mWifi[38;5;252m [0m[38;5;252m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                [0m
